Globally diversified natural resource company Glencore has appointed Liz Hewitt as an independent nonexecutive director with immediate effect. Hewitt has over 30 years’ business experience in executive and nonexecutive positions. She began her career as a qualified chartered accountant with Arthur Andersen & Co. She has held various executive positions in private equity companies. Hewitt is currently a nonexecutive director of National Grid. “The directors are very pleased to welcome Liz Hewitt. She brings significant business, financial and investment knowledge and has wide experience of being a member of, and/or chaired, all types of board committees. “Liz’s diverse knowledge and broad range of expertise is a great addition to the boardroom. We look forward to benefiting from her insights and contribution as a director,” chairperson Kalidas Madhavpeddi says.